-- L’Occitane’s Nine-Month Sales Rise 16%, Led by Growth in China
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   G a r v e y
-- 2012-01-30T11:58:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/l-occitane-s-nine-month-sales-rise-16-led-by-growth-in-china.html
L’Occitane International SA (973) , the
Luxembourg-based cosmetics manufacturer and retailer, said its
nine-month sales rose 16 percent, driven by growth in  China ,
 Hong Kong  and  Brazil .  Sales increased to 681.4 million euros ($894 million) for
the nine months ended Dec. 31, 2011, it said in a statement to
the Hong Kong stock exchange today.  Revenue from China rose 58 percent in local-currency terms,
the company said. Hong Kong’s sales grew 37 percent while those
in Brazil climbed 35 percent, it said.  The company opened 138 new stores over the nine-month
period, compared with 108 in the same period a year earlier,
according to the statement. Same-store sales increased 6.2
percent, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Garvey in Hong Kong at 
